1
00:00:36,403 --> 00:00:43,410
ONE DAY BEFORE T&T MOBILE
STOCKHOLDERS' MEETING

2
00:00:45,879 --> 00:00:47,447
Dear brother.

3
00:00:48,081 --> 00:00:51,584
How should I describe what it's like
to live in the suite room here?

4
00:00:52,552 --> 00:00:55,989
Do people's faces change when they live
in comfortable circumstances?

5
00:00:56,356 --> 00:00:58,558
My eyes are shining

6
00:00:59,559 --> 00:01:01,928
and my skin is glowing.

7
00:01:05,265 --> 00:01:09,436
I'm doing great,
so take good care of yourself.

8
00:01:09,803 --> 00:01:14,541
Living in a suite room is
beyond my imagination.

9
00:01:27,053 --> 00:01:28,154
Who is it?

10
00:01:43,169 --> 00:01:45,271
This is strange.
Whenever I come back home,

11
00:01:45,338 --> 00:01:46,940
there's something on the floor.

12
00:01:49,242 --> 00:01:50,410
Is it a thief?

13
00:01:52,412 --> 00:01:53,646
No way.

14
00:01:54,314 --> 00:01:55,882
If thieves have eyes,

15
00:01:56,716 --> 00:01:58,284
they can see what this place looks like.

16
00:02:12,966 --> 00:02:14,734
Gosh, it hurts.

17
00:02:29,716 --> 00:02:30,783
Gosh, you startled me!

18
00:02:31,784 --> 00:02:34,220
I said I'd be back
after swimming for 30 minutes.

19
00:02:34,821 --> 00:02:37,557
I found something amazing,
so I couldn't wait.

20
00:02:37,891 --> 00:02:40,260
Did you stay up all night looking for it?

21
00:02:40,660 --> 00:02:42,929
There are five of them including this one.

22
00:02:44,197 --> 00:02:46,032
Are you sure it will work?

23
00:02:47,967 --> 00:02:48,902
Let me see.

24
00:02:49,802 --> 00:02:50,970
What are you doing?

25
00:02:51,905 --> 00:02:55,341
Well... I think your swimming suit
is too tight.

26
00:02:55,408 --> 00:02:57,210
Of course swimming suits are tight.

27
00:02:58,645 --> 00:03:00,813
Wait. At least put this on.

28
00:03:06,986 --> 00:03:10,390
Get away from my son right now.

29
00:03:16,262 --> 00:03:17,430
Ma'am.

30
00:03:18,331 --> 00:03:20,333
What you just said and did

31
00:03:20,567 --> 00:03:22,936
might be misleading in many ways.

32
00:03:23,002 --> 00:03:24,504
Are you saying you can't?

33
00:03:25,104 --> 00:03:29,209
And what I'm about to say
can be misleading,

34
00:03:30,076 --> 00:03:31,211
but our relationship

35
00:03:31,911 --> 00:03:34,847
is not something that's damaged
by a single word you say.

36
00:03:34,914 --> 00:03:36,549
When you guys were seven,

37
00:03:36,883 --> 00:03:39,652
you started to frequent my place
with Ms. Choe.

38
00:03:40,186 --> 00:03:42,088
I should've separated you two back then.

39
00:03:42,822 --> 00:03:45,959
Then I wouldn't have seen you
raise your hand at the meeting like that.

40
00:03:47,660 --> 00:03:50,263
I thought this situation felt
somewhat familiar.

41
00:03:50,530 --> 00:03:52,865
I remember something similar happened
when I was seven.

42
00:03:53,399 --> 00:03:55,368
That's why I want to handle it
properly this time.

43
00:03:55,969 --> 00:03:57,437
If water doesn't work...

44
00:04:00,106 --> 00:04:01,441
Nothing works better than this.

45
00:04:06,312 --> 00:04:08,414
This might cause a real misunderstanding.

46
00:04:08,514 --> 00:04:11,718
Take this as your severance pay.

47
00:04:11,951 --> 00:04:13,653
Once the stockholder's meeting is over,

48
00:04:13,720 --> 00:04:15,755
resign your position
and leave the company.

49
00:04:16,723 --> 00:04:19,993
You have no sense of shame, but do have
a brain. I believe you know what I mean.

50
00:04:21,194 --> 00:04:22,328
I should get going.

51
00:04:31,537 --> 00:04:32,972
Who is it?

52
00:04:35,241 --> 00:04:36,976
Mr. Gi.

53
00:04:37,043 --> 00:04:38,111
Ms. Jeong.

54
00:04:39,078 --> 00:04:41,314
What happened to your face?

55
00:04:42,382 --> 00:04:43,516
Please come in.

56
00:04:51,291 --> 00:04:52,759
You didn't have coffee, did you?

57
00:04:54,494 --> 00:04:56,029
I think I had a cup here.

58
00:04:56,095 --> 00:04:57,797
Why is the room so messy?

59
00:04:58,231 --> 00:04:59,532
Are you all right?

60
00:05:04,504 --> 00:05:05,905
I don't need to drink coffee.

61
00:05:06,072 --> 00:05:07,206
Where's Min-ik?

62
00:05:08,574 --> 00:05:11,077
He went for a swim,
but he'll be back soon.

63
00:05:12,278 --> 00:05:13,413
Oh, that...

64
00:05:14,013 --> 00:05:16,382
Is it the list of people
who signed a power of attorney?

65
00:05:23,256 --> 00:05:24,424
Park Ok-sun?

66
00:05:24,490 --> 00:05:25,992
Why hasn't she signed it yet?

67
00:05:26,526 --> 00:05:28,594
You said she'd sign it.

68
00:05:28,661 --> 00:05:29,896
She's signing it today.

69
00:05:30,530 --> 00:05:32,665
Really? Are you sure?

70
00:05:32,865 --> 00:05:35,735
She will sign the power of attorney
and not attend the stockholders' meeting.

71
00:05:36,135 --> 00:05:37,337
Right.

72
00:05:37,904 --> 00:05:40,239
By the way, does
Ms. Park Ok-sun's signature matter?

73
00:05:40,773 --> 00:05:43,209
I remember you say that many times.

74
00:05:49,015 --> 00:05:52,185
Park Ok-sun is Veronica Park's real name.

75
00:05:52,952 --> 00:05:54,520
-Really?
-Who?

76
00:05:56,155 --> 00:05:57,156
My goodness.

77
00:05:57,490 --> 00:05:59,726
What were you whispering about?

78
00:06:00,927 --> 00:06:01,994
Is it a secret?

79
00:06:02,795 --> 00:06:03,896
A conspiracy?

80
00:06:04,430 --> 00:06:05,598
Love?

81
00:06:06,332 --> 00:06:08,434
Coffee.

82
00:06:09,335 --> 00:06:13,473
Mr. Gi wants to drink some coffee, so...

83
00:06:17,377 --> 00:06:18,511
What are you doing here?

84
00:06:18,811 --> 00:06:20,413
Are you here to tell me that you'll quit?

85
00:06:20,813 --> 00:06:22,982
I'm here to see
if you're doing a good job.

86
00:06:23,249 --> 00:06:25,284
What did you make her do
for the past two weeks?

87
00:06:25,351 --> 00:06:26,719
Her face is a mess.

88
00:06:29,689 --> 00:06:30,723
What about her face?

89
00:06:31,357 --> 00:06:32,492
Can't you see?

90
00:06:33,393 --> 00:06:36,295
It's like you put a straw on her face

91
00:06:36,429 --> 00:06:38,164
and sucked her soul out of it.

92
00:06:48,608 --> 00:06:49,709
An imprint.

93
00:06:49,776 --> 00:06:52,011
It's not your eyes that see her face.

94
00:06:52,078 --> 00:06:55,047
It's your brain that's imprinted with her.

95
00:06:56,816 --> 00:06:58,684
I can recognize her face,

96
00:06:59,285 --> 00:07:01,254
but it's not like
I can see her facial expression.

97
00:07:02,588 --> 00:07:04,590
Mr. Do, why...

98
00:07:08,828 --> 00:07:10,897
-Go.
-What? All of a sudden...

99
00:07:11,431 --> 00:07:12,565
Did I do something wrong?

100
00:07:12,732 --> 00:07:15,802
You've been staying
in this suite room the whole time.

101
00:07:16,235 --> 00:07:17,770
Can't you let me use it
at least one night?

102
00:07:18,070 --> 00:07:20,573
The meeting will be held in this hotel
tomorrow anyway.

103
00:07:21,207 --> 00:07:24,944
I think I will feel better
if I stay here tonight.

104
00:07:25,378 --> 00:07:26,879
I guess you're right,

105
00:07:26,946 --> 00:07:28,548
but we still need to practice...

106
00:07:36,289 --> 00:07:39,325
These are the slippers and shampoos
you've been collecting.

107
00:07:41,394 --> 00:07:43,763
Take them all and get some sleep.

108
00:07:45,731 --> 00:07:47,266
I heard they are not free.

109
00:07:48,901 --> 00:07:50,303
If I don't use the minibar in a suite,

110
00:07:50,369 --> 00:07:52,038
it will be embarrassing when I check out.

111
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:57,743
I can't eat this anyway
because it has peanuts in it.

112
00:07:59,378 --> 00:08:00,446
No, it doesn't.

113
00:08:01,781 --> 00:08:04,083
"This product was produced in the factory

114
00:08:04,150 --> 00:08:05,718
that produces peanuts."

115
00:08:10,690 --> 00:08:11,891
Take the hotel limousine.

116
00:08:11,958 --> 00:08:14,227
-I can take a bus.
-Just do as I say.

117
00:08:14,794 --> 00:08:17,096
You're a guest in a suite.
Don't embarrass me.

118
00:08:17,730 --> 00:08:20,199
Don't walk to the bus stop
carrying a bag full of slippers.

119
00:08:22,201 --> 00:08:23,503
Call me when you get home.

120
00:08:24,871 --> 00:08:25,938
Okay.

121
00:08:27,340 --> 00:08:28,441
Go.

122
00:08:28,975 --> 00:08:30,576
I'm going.

123
00:08:30,643 --> 00:08:32,979
Just go. Go home.

124
00:08:46,559 --> 00:08:47,593
Why?

125
00:08:48,928 --> 00:08:50,530
Why don't you drive her home?

126
00:08:52,565 --> 00:08:54,734
What kind of boss
drives his secretary home?

127
00:09:06,679 --> 00:09:09,315
"I should be sorry

128
00:09:09,749 --> 00:09:12,585
to have that voice fall silent

129
00:09:12,919 --> 00:09:15,721
and pass out of my life."

130
00:09:16,155 --> 00:09:17,189
Do you remember?

131
00:09:17,390 --> 00:09:19,525
It's Mark Twain.
We wrote an essay about it in college.

132
00:09:19,592 --> 00:09:21,160
The diaries of Adam and Eve.

133
00:09:21,227 --> 00:09:23,195
What kind of poetic nonsense is that?

134
00:09:23,262 --> 00:09:24,997
Looking at you being like that,

135
00:09:25,264 --> 00:09:27,099
I just remembered this quote.

136
00:09:28,100 --> 00:09:30,436
Watching Ms. Jeong leave,

137
00:09:31,404 --> 00:09:33,472
you seemed really sad.

138
00:09:35,474 --> 00:09:36,576
You're crazy.

139
00:09:37,643 --> 00:09:39,946
We've been through a lot together
for the past two weeks.

140
00:09:40,012 --> 00:09:42,648
It's my camaraderie toward my secretary.

141
00:09:42,715 --> 00:09:44,450
She stayed in a suite for the first time.

142
00:09:44,517 --> 00:09:45,751
It's my love for humanity.

143
00:09:46,018 --> 00:09:48,454
And it's philanthropy of Do Min-ik

144
00:09:48,521 --> 00:09:49,689
who loves all human beings.

145
00:09:53,426 --> 00:09:54,493
Are you sure it's not dating?

146
00:09:54,594 --> 00:09:57,663
There's someone else I'd like to date.

147
00:09:57,897 --> 00:09:58,998
Is there?

148
00:09:59,498 --> 00:10:00,600
Who is it?

149
00:10:04,737 --> 00:10:05,905
The thing is...

150
00:10:07,406 --> 00:10:10,009
I didn't even know

151
00:10:10,509 --> 00:10:12,912
I'd grow to like her this much.

152
00:10:13,713 --> 00:10:15,414
When I think of you,

153
00:10:16,449 --> 00:10:19,418
my stomach feels somewhat heavy.

154
00:10:21,454 --> 00:10:23,289
I think I have indigestion.

155
00:10:24,056 --> 00:10:27,393
Every time I look at her,
my heart starts pounding.

156
00:10:27,994 --> 00:10:30,563
It feels like my blood pressure goes up.

157
00:10:31,263 --> 00:10:32,398
Is she pretty?

158
00:10:36,936 --> 00:10:38,037
She's pretty.

159
00:10:38,371 --> 00:10:39,972
It's a little strange though.

160
00:10:41,007 --> 00:10:42,808
Her voice sounds familiar.

161
00:10:43,275 --> 00:10:45,011
Even when I first met her,

162
00:10:45,745 --> 00:10:49,715
it felt like she knew me.

163
00:10:50,216 --> 00:10:52,018
You totally fell for her.

164
00:10:52,351 --> 00:10:53,352
Hey.

165
00:10:56,122 --> 00:10:57,456
You should call her.

166
00:10:57,823 --> 00:10:59,592
Let me hear her voice.

167
00:11:00,693 --> 00:11:02,028
The stockholders' meeting is tomorrow.

168
00:11:02,094 --> 00:11:03,462
I don't have time for this.

169
00:11:03,929 --> 00:11:05,064
Just go.

170
00:11:05,297 --> 00:11:07,366
I know you want to tell me
that you're going to quit.

171
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:09,802
You can just at least call her.

172
00:11:12,405 --> 00:11:13,506
Here.

173
00:11:14,707 --> 00:11:16,242
Did I borrow money from you?

174
00:11:16,542 --> 00:11:18,444
I did, from your mom.

175
00:11:18,644 --> 00:11:21,147
She lent me this
knowing I was in need of money.

176
00:11:23,182 --> 00:11:24,817
Give my thanks to your mom.

177
00:11:30,089 --> 00:11:31,857
And make sure to be well prepared.

178
00:11:35,061 --> 00:11:37,930
Even if I quit, you will still be...

179
00:11:39,665 --> 00:11:41,067
You know Cho PD's song.

180
00:11:42,468 --> 00:11:43,502
"Friend."

181
00:11:48,974 --> 00:11:51,577
Hurray!

182
00:11:55,681 --> 00:11:58,718
Isn't this a perfect place for a date?

183
00:12:00,352 --> 00:12:02,288
It's a perfect place to sign.

184
00:12:05,491 --> 00:12:07,426
If I sign this document,

185
00:12:07,693 --> 00:12:11,163
I wonder what I can get from you.

186
00:12:11,230 --> 00:12:12,865
Even if I don't get you anything.

187
00:12:12,932 --> 00:12:15,034
you already have everything you need.

188
00:12:15,101 --> 00:12:17,336
Even though I have everything I need,

189
00:12:17,403 --> 00:12:21,073
I don't have anything that came from you.
That's why I'm asking.

190
00:12:21,741 --> 00:12:24,844
I can buy you a meal if you don't mind.

191
00:12:26,178 --> 00:12:29,515
A meal for 100,000 shares?

192
00:12:31,450 --> 00:12:33,252
I guess that's not bad.

193
00:12:33,886 --> 00:12:35,955
As you already know,

194
00:12:36,021 --> 00:12:38,390
I like stuff with rip-off prices.

195
00:12:44,964 --> 00:12:46,265
By the way,

196
00:12:47,566 --> 00:12:49,635
am I signing the power of attorney

197
00:12:49,702 --> 00:12:51,570
to oppose

198
00:12:51,904 --> 00:12:55,307
the dismissal of Director Do Min-ik?

199
00:12:55,941 --> 00:12:57,743
Are you saying you can't trust me?

200
00:12:57,810 --> 00:13:00,412
I mean I can't trust myself.

201
00:13:00,579 --> 00:13:03,883
There have been like 12 times
when I made wrong choices

202
00:13:04,917 --> 00:13:07,119
because of men.

203
00:13:07,419 --> 00:13:09,455
If that's the case,
you don't have to worry.

204
00:13:09,588 --> 00:13:11,590
I've never lost my reason

205
00:13:11,657 --> 00:13:13,125
because of women.

206
00:13:13,225 --> 00:13:15,161
Too bad.

207
00:13:16,262 --> 00:13:21,667
I just forgot how to sign.

208
00:13:29,375 --> 00:13:31,210
This is how.

209
00:13:36,115 --> 00:13:37,750
When are you buying me a meal?

210
00:13:38,284 --> 00:13:41,120
I don't like to pay in advance.

211
00:13:46,826 --> 00:13:48,761
I hope you will spare the time
to meet me tomorrow.

212
00:13:49,495 --> 00:13:52,097
I'll treat you to a meal
after the stockholders' meeting.

213
00:13:53,065 --> 00:13:54,166
Yes.

214
00:13:54,466 --> 00:13:57,036
I checked the file, and nothing's wrong.

215
00:13:57,970 --> 00:13:59,972
No. You don't have to come.

216
00:14:00,406 --> 00:14:01,974
I'll bring it there.

