00:35:12,543 --> 00:35:15,179
What do you mean?

536
00:35:15,746 --> 00:35:20,017
Your eyes are not asking me
to save your boss.

537
00:35:20,284 --> 00:35:22,887
It's more like they are asking me
to save your man.

538
00:35:23,688 --> 00:35:26,224
Well... It's not like that.

539
00:35:27,558 --> 00:35:29,093
We've been working together,

540
00:35:29,160 --> 00:35:31,062
so I respect him as my boss--

541
00:35:32,063 --> 00:35:34,832
If that's how you look
when you admire someone,

542
00:35:34,899 --> 00:35:37,902
I guess you will just melt the statue
of Admiral Yi Sun-sin in Gwanghwamun.

543
00:35:39,637 --> 00:35:42,573
You never know how you look
by looking into a mirror.

544
00:35:43,107 --> 00:35:44,909
Only people around you can see it right.

545
00:35:45,510 --> 00:35:48,379
Hey, I wish I could bring some lame actor

546
00:35:48,446 --> 00:35:51,415
and let him see how your eyes look now.

547
00:35:52,016 --> 00:35:56,420
To tell him that this is exactly
how you look when you are in love.

548
00:35:59,490 --> 00:36:00,892
Who's that bitch?

549
00:36:01,359 --> 00:36:03,728
It's Park Seok-ja, your mom.

550
00:36:05,163 --> 00:36:07,131
Chairwoman Park, hello.

551
00:36:07,331 --> 00:36:10,234
Is this a school reunion or what?
Why are you chatting away here?

552
00:36:10,568 --> 00:36:11,736
Just stand up.

553
00:36:12,170 --> 00:36:15,339
We should go and say hello
to Chairwoman Sim and Mr. Do.

554
00:36:16,307 --> 00:36:17,608
Let me see.

555
00:36:18,075 --> 00:36:22,713
I think I saw Mr. Do somewhere here.

556
00:36:25,783 --> 00:36:26,784
Mr. Do.

557
00:36:26,851 --> 00:36:28,452
Who was the woman sitting next to you?

558
00:36:28,986 --> 00:36:30,488
Why did she ask questions?

559
00:36:30,555 --> 00:36:32,123
Just get in there.

560
00:36:32,190 --> 00:36:33,791
VOTING BOOTH

561
00:36:36,594 --> 00:36:39,730
Jeong Gal-hee, what are you doing now?

562
00:36:40,364 --> 00:36:42,500
-What are you doing?
-I'm not sure.

563
00:36:43,201 --> 00:36:45,236
What am I doing now?

564
00:36:45,736 --> 00:36:47,605
We spent two weeks together,

565
00:36:49,073 --> 00:36:50,508
so now you want to vote together?

566
00:36:50,575 --> 00:36:53,077
Do we have to do that in this small booth?

567
00:36:54,011 --> 00:36:55,179
Just go ahead and do it.

568
00:36:57,982 --> 00:36:59,817
Actually, I have a place to go.

569
00:37:00,151 --> 00:37:01,319
A place to go?

570
00:37:06,824 --> 00:37:08,092
Here. Let's go.

571
00:37:08,559 --> 00:37:09,660
Wait.

572
00:37:19,337 --> 00:37:22,206
Now. We should go. Please hurry.

573
00:37:23,140 --> 00:37:26,344
Nice to meet you. I'm Veronica Park.

574
00:37:31,816 --> 00:37:33,551
Please excuse her.

575
00:37:34,218 --> 00:37:35,353
I should've

576
00:37:35,419 --> 00:37:37,922
taught her some manners
when she was young.

577
00:37:38,122 --> 00:37:39,957
You know it, right?

578
00:37:40,024 --> 00:37:42,827
I was so busy working for T&T Mobile

579
00:37:42,893 --> 00:37:44,428
that I didn't have time

580
00:37:44,495 --> 00:37:46,364
to take care of my daughter.

581
00:37:48,065 --> 00:37:51,435
And your daughter made Seokja Corporation

582
00:37:51,702 --> 00:37:54,705
into the biggest
cultural company in the company.

583
00:37:58,009 --> 00:38:00,278
Nice to meet you. I'm Sim Hae-ra.

584
00:38:02,647 --> 00:38:05,716
I heard you are getting along with my son.

585
00:38:06,984 --> 00:38:08,152
I am?

586
00:38:10,421 --> 00:38:14,091
So did he tell his mother
that I was actually there?

587
00:38:14,292 --> 00:38:15,359
Yes.

588
00:38:15,660 --> 00:38:19,063
As if you two actually met last night.

589
00:38:21,565 --> 00:38:23,534
Well... Yes.

590
00:38:24,268 --> 00:38:27,605
My daughter doesn't usually attend
meetings like this.

591
00:38:27,905 --> 00:38:31,242
But she came here to meet your son today.

592
00:38:31,342 --> 00:38:34,011
Oh, is that so?

593
00:38:35,313 --> 00:38:37,014
Then you should say hello to him.

594
00:38:37,481 --> 00:38:38,949
Where did he go?

595
00:38:42,653 --> 00:38:44,121
Where are you going?

596
00:38:46,957 --> 00:38:48,559
-Give me your phone.
-What?

597
00:38:48,626 --> 00:38:50,027
Just give it to me.

598
00:38:53,331 --> 00:38:54,632
Mr. Do...

599
00:39:03,107 --> 00:39:04,141
Get in.

600
00:39:04,275 --> 00:39:06,177
Where are we going?

601
00:39:06,243 --> 00:39:07,578
It's still working hours.

602
00:39:07,645 --> 00:39:09,780
Are you refusing to come with me?

603
00:39:11,082 --> 00:39:12,116
Get in.

604
00:39:16,754 --> 00:39:18,489
How are the stockholders?

605
00:39:19,056 --> 00:39:20,057
Is everything all right?

606
00:39:20,124 --> 00:39:23,160
I guess a few of them are shaken.

607
00:39:23,227 --> 00:39:25,496
But they are just small investors.

608
00:39:25,830 --> 00:39:28,866
The major stockholders have already
made up their minds.

609
00:39:28,933 --> 00:39:31,268
We're already done calculating
the votes in favor.

610
00:39:31,335 --> 00:39:32,703
You don't have to worry.

611
00:39:33,738 --> 00:39:36,173
The problem is

612
00:39:36,240 --> 00:39:39,310
that we don't know
what the lady would vote for.

613
00:39:40,678 --> 00:39:42,446
Let me get this straight.

614
00:39:43,314 --> 00:39:45,282
If I go to your stockholders' meeting

615
00:39:45,349 --> 00:39:48,018
and vote for you,

616
00:39:48,285 --> 00:39:50,287
you will come to our stockholders' meeting

617
00:39:50,354 --> 00:39:52,757
and vote for my consecutive appointment?

618
00:39:52,890 --> 00:39:55,459
So it's like I scratch your back
and you'll scratch mine.

619
00:39:55,526 --> 00:39:56,827
Let's say it's a friendship.

620
00:39:56,894 --> 00:39:58,129
I should never be inhospitable

621
00:39:58,195 --> 00:40:01,031
to someone to whom I'm indebted.

622
00:40:01,599 --> 00:40:02,666
Do you know

623
00:40:02,733 --> 00:40:05,369
I recently purchased
another 80,000 stocks of Cinepark?

624
00:40:10,141 --> 00:40:11,242
Ms. Park.

625
00:40:12,009 --> 00:40:14,311
Gosh, Mr. Sim.

626
00:40:14,412 --> 00:40:16,414
Make sure to do your math right.

627
00:40:17,181 --> 00:40:20,117
Don't get swayed by something useless
and lose your money.

628
00:40:20,184 --> 00:40:21,519
Of course.

629
00:40:21,952 --> 00:40:25,456
I don't want to make a wrong choice

630
00:40:25,523 --> 00:40:28,426
because of a guy 13 times.

631
00:40:39,870 --> 00:40:43,207
Your destination is 2km away.

632
00:40:44,041 --> 00:40:45,943
Where are we going now?

633
00:40:48,012 --> 00:40:50,347
Will you at least give me back my phone?

634
00:40:50,414 --> 00:40:52,216
How dare you touch me?
Keep your hands off me.

635
00:40:52,650 --> 00:40:54,151
Are you kidnapping me?

636
00:40:54,351 --> 00:40:57,455
Your wish is to have some soju
with grilled clams

637
00:40:57,655 --> 00:40:59,957
after the stockholder's meeting.

638
00:41:01,892 --> 00:41:04,361
Listen, Mr. Do. I'm the one

639
00:41:04,428 --> 00:41:06,764
who feels extremely nervous and afraid

640
00:41:06,831 --> 00:41:08,799
to be at the meeting.

641
00:41:09,300 --> 00:41:11,802
But I don't think we should be doing this.

642
00:41:11,902 --> 00:41:12,903
Just turn the car around.

643
00:41:13,871 --> 00:41:15,539
Would this help you relax?

644
00:41:16,040 --> 00:41:19,543
We have another good reason
to have a celebration party

645
00:41:19,810 --> 00:41:21,078
besides the stockholders' meeting.

646
00:41:22,179 --> 00:41:23,314
What is it?

647
00:41:31,422 --> 00:41:32,490
I can see them.

648
00:41:43,701 --> 00:41:45,836
T&T MOBILE EXTRAORDINARY
STOCKHOLDERS' MEETING

649
00:41:51,008 --> 00:41:53,377
I will announce the results of the vote.

650
00:41:53,878 --> 00:41:59,750
A total of 125,116,807 stocks
participated in the vote.

651
00:41:59,817 --> 00:42:03,420
And a total of five thousand...

652
00:42:15,432 --> 00:42:16,467
Here.

653
00:42:17,101 --> 00:42:18,569
Do you want me to grill them?

654
00:42:18,636 --> 00:42:20,271
Sure. Do you want me to do it?

655
00:42:20,337 --> 00:42:22,540
Your boss just drove you all the way here.

656
00:42:23,007 --> 00:42:24,675
You should be grateful.

657
00:42:25,609 --> 00:42:27,778
I guess you are mistaken about something.

658
00:42:27,845 --> 00:42:30,381
When I said I wanted to eat grilled clams,

659
00:42:30,447 --> 00:42:32,016
I meant I wanted to do it

660
00:42:32,082 --> 00:42:34,585
with someone I like
listening to the sound of waves.

661
00:42:34,785 --> 00:42:36,287
I didn't want to put on these gloves

662
00:42:36,654 --> 00:42:39,156
and grill clams for my boss.

663
00:42:43,327 --> 00:42:46,797
Here. Would this work?

664
00:42:58,042 --> 00:42:59,944
You know the flash drive I told you about?

665
00:43:00,010 --> 00:43:02,646
I looked for it everywhere,
but I couldn't find it.

666
00:43:03,180 --> 00:43:04,548
-You couldn't?
-No.

667
00:43:04,882 --> 00:43:07,351
I'm sure I put it in my drawer,
but it's not there.

668
00:43:07,718 --> 00:43:10,588
I have the copy
of the file in my laptop though.

669
00:43:10,654 --> 00:43:14,091
It was in the suit you wore
on the day of the accident.

670
00:43:14,158 --> 00:43:16,093
I was afraid it might be broken.

671
00:43:25,035 --> 00:43:27,237
The result should be out by now.

672
00:43:34,378 --> 00:43:36,313
If you won, this is a celebratory drink.

673
00:43:36,947 --> 00:43:39,950
If you didn't,
it should be a consolation drink.

674
00:43:44,888 --> 00:43:48,425
Therefore, dismissal
of Director Do Min-ik...

675
00:43:48,826 --> 00:43:51,161
RESULTS OF THE VOTE

676
00:43:58,869 --> 00:44:00,504
MISTER'S GRILLED CLAMS

677
00:44:00,571 --> 00:44:02,039
What are you thinking about?

678
00:44:03,173 --> 00:44:06,276
Even in this peaceful scenery,

679
00:44:07,077 --> 00:44:09,580
a human's mind can be so complicated.

680
00:44:10,114 --> 00:44:11,415
What about you?

681
00:44:13,450 --> 00:44:15,486
I'm glad that I came here with you.

682
00:44:23,594 --> 00:44:26,163
Grilled clams taste great
when my secretary cooks them.

683
00:44:31,635 --> 00:44:34,271
They look so happy.

684
00:44:34,738 --> 00:44:36,073
Aren't they fighting?

685
00:44:36,140 --> 00:44:37,408
They are having fun.

686
00:44:37,474 --> 00:44:39,143
The face of the woman says...

687
00:44:44,148 --> 00:44:47,317
You never know how you look
by looking into a mirror.

688
00:44:48,118 --> 00:44:49,787
Only people around you can see it right.

689
00:44:51,455 --> 00:44:52,589
She's right.

690
00:44:54,692 --> 00:44:58,062
Now I can see what she looks like.

691
00:45:00,130 --> 00:45:01,231
See what?

692
00:45:02,766 --> 00:45:03,701
Nothing.

693
00:45:03,767 --> 00:45:07,371
What is it you were trying to say earlier?

694
00:45:07,438 --> 00:45:08,872
Besides the meeting,

695
00:45:08,939 --> 00:45:11,642
we have something else to celebrate.

696
00:45:15,379 --> 00:45:16,447
The thing is,

697
00:45:17,147 --> 00:45:20,484
on the stage, even though
it was only for a short period of time...

698
00:45:21,685 --> 00:45:22,986
Hang on.

699
00:45:23,253 --> 00:45:24,521
GI DAE-JU

700
00:45:27,157 --> 00:45:28,525
The result must be out.

701
00:45:29,460 --> 00:45:30,594
Answer it.

702
00:45:32,029 --> 00:45:33,697
Just answer the phone.

703
00:45:39,036 --> 00:45:40,304
Where are you?

704
00:45:40,471 --> 00:45:41,572
Yes.

705
00:45:42,439 --> 00:45:43,607
Okay.

706
00:45:44,575 --> 00:45:45,843
Okay. Bye.

707
00:45:52,483 --> 00:45:53,650
What did he say?

708
00:45:54,184 --> 00:45:55,319
Ms. Jeong.

709
00:45:56,687 --> 00:46:00,290
Is the bird flying over there
is a seagull or a wild goose?

710
00:46:00,457 --> 00:46:02,359
Gosh, Mr. Do.

711
00:46:03,127 --> 00:46:04,228
What is it?

712
00:46:05,095 --> 00:46:06,864
Was the drink we had earlier

713
00:46:07,798 --> 00:46:08,999
a celebratory drink?

714
00:46:10,134 --> 00:46:11,969
Or a consolation drink?

715
00:46:20,778 --> 00:46:21,879
A celebratory drink.

716
00:46:25,415 --> 00:46:26,550
"A celebratory drink"?

717
00:46:27,484 --> 00:46:29,720
Congratulations, Mr. Do.

718
00:46:29,920 --> 00:46:31,321
I'm so happy for you.

719
00:47:18,502 --> 00:47:21,305
You did a great job, Ms. Jeong.

720
00:47:42,559 --> 00:47:43,927
I have a gift for you.

721
00:47:45,662 --> 00:47:47,698
I was going to give it to you
before the result came out.

722
00:47:50,033 --> 00:47:51,101
Here.

723
00:47:53,737 --> 00:47:55,038
Open the trunk.

724
00:47:55,172 --> 00:47:56,273
The trunk?

725
00:47:57,574 --> 00:47:59,443
Why did you keep a gift in the trunk?

726
00:48:05,315 --> 00:48:10,053
MISTER'S GRILLED CLAMS

727
00:48:10,120 --> 00:48:11,655
Gosh.

728
00:48:12,356 --> 00:48:16,260
Are there a thousand roses
and a thousand balloons in the trunk?

729
00:48:17,294 --> 00:48:20,030
I don't like a surprise like that.

730
00:48:25,469 --> 00:48:27,604
What? There's nothing.

731
00:48:28,205 --> 00:48:30,407
There is something. Look carefully.

732
00:48:31,942 --> 00:48:33,677
What's in there?

733
00:48:39,516 --> 00:48:40,617
Is this it?

734
00:48:49,126 --> 00:48:50,260
T&T MOBILE STOCKHOLDERS' MEETING

735
00:48:50,327 --> 00:48:51,962
Min-ik gets to stay.

736
00:48:56,533 --> 00:48:57,968
Well done, Min-ik.

737
00:49:02,072 --> 00:49:03,073
CEO SIM HAE-YONG

738
00:49:13,317 --> 00:49:14,584
Mr. Gi Dae-ju?

739
00:49:15,152 --> 00:49:17,854
Where are we having dinner tonight?

740
00:49:18,055 --> 00:49:21,458
I think I deserve something
for my 100,000 stocks.

741
00:49:21,725 --> 00:49:24,261
-But...
-But?

742
00:49:28,432 --> 00:49:29,900
Did I tell you this?

743
00:49:30,901 --> 00:49:32,269
I'm a jerk.

744
00:49:33,804 --> 00:49:35,205
Even worse than you think.

745
00:49:38,775 --> 00:49:41,845
I'm sorry, but I can't have
dinner with you tonight.

746
00:49:49,786 --> 00:49:51,421
He's so attractive.

747
00:50:03,066 --> 00:50:05,235
Well... I'm really nervous.

748
00:50:05,302 --> 00:50:07,738
Can I just open it here?

749
00:50:08,271 --> 00:50:10,874
I told you to open it when you get home.

750
00:50:11,575 --> 00:50:13,744
Gosh, I'm so curious.

751
00:50:13,810 --> 00:50:15,278
How much would it be?

752
00:50:15,712 --> 00:50:16,813
How much?

753
00:50:17,581 --> 00:50:19,583
Isn't this money?

754
00:50:21,685 --> 00:50:24,621
In your common sense,
the only thing that can be in an envelope

755
00:50:24,988 --> 00:50:26,456
is money?

756
00:50:26,923 --> 00:50:29,059
Can't you expand your mind?

757
00:50:31,595 --> 00:50:32,963
No way.

758
00:50:34,164 --> 00:50:35,432
Is it a handwritten letter?

759
00:50:37,768 --> 00:50:39,870
It's the most useless thing.

760
00:50:41,171 --> 00:50:45,142
If you had something to tell me,
you could've texted me.

761
00:50:46,610 --> 00:50:48,879
Gosh, just open it.

762
00:50:50,247 --> 00:50:51,281
Gosh.

763
00:50:56,386 --> 00:50:58,455
EMPLOYMENT CONTRACT

764
00:50:58,922 --> 00:51:00,157
A contract?

765
00:51:04,027 --> 00:51:06,997
I'm going to say this only once,
so listen carefully.

766
00:51:07,931 --> 00:51:09,499
I had a secretary.

767
00:51:10,367 --> 00:51:11,468
Three years ago.

768
00:51:13,904 --> 00:51:17,507
I trusted and relied on my secretary.

769
00:51:18,408 --> 00:51:20,177
But at the most important moment,

770
00:51:21,144 --> 00:51:23,914
she deceived and betrayed me.

771
00:51:26,049 --> 00:51:28,351
That's when I started trying my best.

772
00:51:29,052 --> 00:51:30,153
I decided

773
00:51:31,121 --> 00:51:32,689
not to trust my secretary anymore.

774
00:51:35,759 --> 00:51:37,060
I know

775
00:51:38,195 --> 00:51:40,864
I tried to fire you, hated you,

776
00:51:41,698 --> 00:51:43,400
bullied you, and gave you a hard time.

777
00:51:45,035 --> 00:51:46,837
But it's not like I hated you.

778
00:51:48,805 --> 00:51:50,273
I hated that secretary.

779
00:51:53,443 --> 00:51:55,145
It's her who deceived me.

780
00:51:56,513 --> 00:51:58,381
It wasn't even your fault.

781
00:52:02,486 --> 00:52:03,720
Still,

782
00:52:05,589 --> 00:52:07,124
I was afraid you'd be like her.

783
00:52:09,059 --> 00:52:11,328
I just did it because I was worried.

784
00:52:13,763 --> 00:52:17,534
If I did anything to upset you,
please try to understand me.

785
00:52:19,703 --> 00:52:22,706
And if you are interested,

786
00:52:24,508 --> 00:52:26,209
I'd like to renew our contract.

787
00:52:28,678 --> 00:52:29,946
What do I do?

788
00:52:30,947 --> 00:52:32,983
I'm deceiving you too.

789
00:52:34,951 --> 00:52:37,154
You'll see once you read it.

790
00:52:38,121 --> 00:52:40,991
"As soon as my disease
is cured, the contract

791
00:52:41,358 --> 00:52:42,993
between you and me will be terminated."

792
00:52:43,293 --> 00:52:48,331
I changed this article
into something better.

793
00:52:50,734 --> 00:52:53,270
THE CONTRACT WILL BE TERMINATED
WHEN THE EMPLOYEE ASKS

794
00:52:53,670 --> 00:52:56,540
"The contract will be terminated

795
00:52:57,240 --> 00:52:59,376
when the employee asks."

796
00:53:04,347 --> 00:53:05,615
Mr. Do.

797
00:53:05,682 --> 00:53:09,586
What do you think? You feel thrilled,
and your heart is pounding, right?

798
00:53:11,955 --> 00:53:15,959
Why? It's the only thing
you wanted from me.

799
00:53:16,426 --> 00:53:18,395
Stable employment.

800
00:53:20,363 --> 00:53:22,165
I can imagine

801
00:53:22,432 --> 00:53:24,501
what your face looks like now.

802
00:53:27,103 --> 00:53:29,439
For your boss
who can't read your expression,

803
00:53:30,173 --> 00:53:33,777
can you explain to me
about the look on your face

804
00:53:33,843 --> 00:53:35,178
in details?

805
00:53:36,246 --> 00:53:37,314
Well...

806
00:53:40,283 --> 00:53:41,351
The thing is...

807
00:53:44,588 --> 00:53:45,922
I'm smiling.

808
00:53:47,324 --> 00:53:50,227
With a beam of satisfaction.

809
00:53:55,265 --> 00:53:57,567
I have a wide grin on my face.

810
00:54:00,904 --> 00:54:02,872
The middle of my forehead is smoothed.

811
00:54:06,142 --> 00:54:10,046
And I got wrinkles around my eyes.

812
00:54:10,914 --> 00:54:12,415
Because I smiled so much.

813
00:54:22,926 --> 00:54:24,094
If...

814
00:54:25,662 --> 00:54:27,097
What if...

815
00:54:30,533 --> 00:54:33,603
What if I'm deceiving you too?

816
00:54:35,672 --> 00:54:36,740
What?

817
00:54:37,140 --> 00:54:38,375
What if

818
00:54:39,376 --> 00:54:42,712
there's something I'm lying to you about?

819
00:54:53,556 --> 00:54:54,858
Then...

820
00:54:57,260 --> 00:54:58,361
I will never

821
00:55:01,097 --> 00:55:02,866
be able to trust others
for the rest of my life.

822
00:55:07,737 --> 00:55:08,972
Hang on.

823
00:55:10,640 --> 00:55:11,841
Hello?

824
00:55:12,509 --> 00:55:14,844
You did a good job. Where are you?

825
00:55:15,412 --> 00:55:17,213
I stepped outside for a bit.

826
00:55:17,380 --> 00:55:20,950
We're going to have dinner.
I want you to come.

827
00:55:21,251 --> 00:55:22,919
"We"? Who are you with?

828
00:55:23,053 --> 00:55:24,621
Did you not see her earlier?

829
00:55:26,189 --> 00:55:28,625
Veronica says she came here to see you.

830
00:55:29,092 --> 00:55:32,162
Veronica came to see me?

831
00:55:33,496 --> 00:55:35,765
Yes. Okay. Bye.

832
00:55:37,334 --> 00:55:38,535
What do I do?

833
00:55:40,737 --> 00:55:42,072
Are you going?

834
00:55:42,138 --> 00:55:44,808
How long does it take
to get to Seoul from here?

835
00:55:44,941 --> 00:55:46,109
Is there heavy traffic?

836
00:55:49,612 --> 00:55:50,980
Please don't go.

837
00:55:52,549 --> 00:55:53,616
What?

838
00:55:54,551 --> 00:55:56,152
I don't want you to go.

839
00:55:56,953 --> 00:55:58,088
Why?

840
00:56:00,757 --> 00:56:04,661
I don't know where I should begin.

841
00:56:04,728 --> 00:56:07,097
Whether it's an excuse or explanation,
I'll hear it later.

842
00:56:07,163 --> 00:56:10,633
Shall we just go now?

843
00:56:13,403 --> 00:56:15,672
Do you want to see her that badly?

844
00:56:15,839 --> 00:56:17,140
Did you not hear me?

845
00:56:17,307 --> 00:56:19,943
Veronica came to see me.

846
00:56:22,278 --> 00:56:25,248
I want to go. I want to see her.

847
00:56:33,890 --> 00:56:34,958
Okay.

848
00:56:36,459 --> 00:56:37,494
You should go.

849
00:56:38,895 --> 00:56:41,931
Instead of hearing it from me here,

850
00:56:43,700 --> 00:56:46,002
you should go and see it yourself.

851
00:56:47,604 --> 00:56:48,671
That's right.

852
00:57:02,752 --> 00:57:03,853
Hurry.

853
00:57:19,002 --> 00:57:21,004
What? Aren't you getting in?

854
00:57:22,505 --> 00:57:24,040
I'm not going.

855
00:57:24,541 --> 00:57:25,575
What?

856
00:57:27,377 --> 00:57:28,945
I'll stay here and sober up.

857
00:57:29,012 --> 00:57:30,547
You go first.

858
00:57:37,220 --> 00:57:38,788
The sun is setting soon.

859
00:57:39,422 --> 00:57:40,924
How would you go home by yourself?

860
00:57:42,792 --> 00:57:45,295
I put a bottle of water
on the passenger seat.

861
00:57:45,361 --> 00:57:47,297
Drink it when you're thirsty.

862
00:57:48,598 --> 00:57:50,366
You're almost running out of gas.

863
00:57:50,767 --> 00:57:53,236
Make sure to fill it up
before getting on the expressway.

864
00:57:53,937 --> 00:57:56,739
Don't drive too fast
because you're in a rush.

865
00:57:57,407 --> 00:57:58,441
And...

866
00:58:02,412 --> 00:58:03,480
Well...

867
00:58:05,148 --> 00:58:09,419
When you're talking to Veronica Park,

868
00:58:11,321 --> 00:58:14,557
you might want to hear something from me.

869
00:58:16,392 --> 00:58:18,995
Then feel free to call me anytime.

870
00:58:21,130 --> 00:58:22,899
I'll tell you everything.

871
00:58:23,700 --> 00:58:26,069
Do you know that you're being
really strange now?

872
00:58:28,104 --> 00:58:30,607
You said a bottle of soju
isn't enough to get you drunk.

873
00:58:34,310 --> 00:58:36,980
You should go
before the traffic jam becomes worse.

874
00:59:43,479 --> 00:59:46,149
Did you meet Veronica Park?

875
00:59:46,215 --> 00:59:47,083
Let's end it.

876
00:59:47,150 --> 00:59:49,252
The relationship between your boss and me.

877
00:59:49,953 --> 00:59:52,722
Does this mean you don't want to work
for me

878
00:59:52,789 --> 00:59:54,023
-anymore?
-Yes.

879
00:59:54,090 --> 00:59:55,258
"Yes"?

880
00:59:56,059 --> 00:59:57,260
Ms. Jeong.

881
00:59:57,527 --> 01:00:01,364
Can you stay by my side?

882
